Package uk.co.terminological.rjava.types

Class RDataframe

java.lang.Object
java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
java.util.HashMap<K,V>
java.util.LinkedHashMap<String,RVector<? extends RPrimitive>>
uk.co.terminological.rjava.types.RDataframe
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<RDataframeRow>, Map<String,RVector<? extends RPrimitive>>, RCollection<RDataframeRow>, RObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
RBoundDataframe
public class RDataframe extends LinkedHashMap<String,RVector<? extends RPrimitive>> implements RCollection<RDataframeRow>
A java equivalent of the R Dataframe organised in column format. This method has various accessors for iterating over or streaming the contents
Version:
$Id: $Id
Author:
terminological

    • mutate

      public <X extends RPrimitive, Y extends RPrimitive> RDataframe mutate(String columnName, Class<X> inputType, Function<X,Y> mapping)
      Returns the same data frame with the column "columnName"
      Type Parameters:
      X - - the R primitive type of the column before the mapping
      Y - - any R primitive type of the column after the mapping
      Parameters:
      columnName - - the name of the column to mutate
      inputType - - the type of the original column
      mapping - - the operation to apply to the column (must result in an RPrimitive of some type)
      Returns:
      the same dataframe with a changed column
